evidence: Percent of Gold = [ count(type = 'gold' and issued date < 1998) / count(all cards)] * 100%
gold-question: How many percent of 'Gold' cards were issued prior to 1998?
gold-sql: SELECT CAST(SUM(type = 'gold') AS REAL) * 100 / COUNT(card_id) FROM card WHERE STRFTIME('%Y', issued) < '1998'

evidence: status = 'C' stands for running contract, OK so far; status = 'D' stands for running contract, client in debt. 'POPLATEK PO OBRATU' stands for issuance after transaction
gold-question: What is the average amount of loan which are still on running contract with statement issuance after each transaction?
gold-sql: SELECT AVG(T2.payments) FROM account AS T1 INNER JOIN loan AS T2 ON T1.account_id = T2.account_id WHERE T2.status IN ('C', 'D') AND T1.frequency = 'POPLATEK PO OBRATU'

gold-question: How many atoms belong to the molecule labeled with carcinogenic compounds?
gold-sql: SELECT COUNT(T1.atom_id) FROM atom AS T1 INNER JOIN molecule AS T2 ON T1.molecule_id = T2.molecule_id WHERE T2.label = '+'

evidence: German refer to language; all types refer to the union of subtypes and supertypes where subtypes is not null AND supertypes is not null
gold-question: Lists all types of cards in German.
gold-sql: SELECT T1.subtypes, T1.supertypes FROM cards AS T1 INNER JOIN foreign_data AS T2 ON T1.uuid = T2.uuid WHERE T2.language = 'German' AND T1.subtypes IS NOT NULL AND T1.supertypes IS NOT NULL

evidence: don't appear in Magic: The Gathering Online refers to mtgoCode is NULL or mtgoCode = ''
gold-question: Please provide top three sets that don't appear in Magic: The Gathering Online, along with their names in in alphabetical order.
gold-sql: SELECT name FROM sets WHERE mtgoCode IS NULL ORDER BY name LIMIT 3

evidence: unknown power refers to power IS NULL or power = '*'; can't be found in foil refers to hasFoil = 0; duel deck A refers to duelDeck = 'a'
gold-question: How many cards with unknown power that can't be found in foil is in duel deck A?
gold-sql: SELECT SUM(CASE WHEN power LIKE '%*%' OR power IS NULL THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) FROM cards WHERE hasFoil = 0 AND duelDeck = 'a'

evidence: format of the cards refers to format; illustrator refers to artist; the least amount of cards refers to MIN(artist)
gold-question: Who is the illustrator that illustrated the least amount of cards? List the format of play of the cards that he/she illustrated.
gold-sql: SELECT T1.artist, T2.format FROM cards AS T1 INNER JOIN legalities AS T2 ON T2.uuid = T1.uuid GROUP BY T1.artist ORDER BY COUNT(T1.id) ASC LIMIT 1

evidence: most valuable post refers to Max(FavoriteCount)
gold-question: What is the display name of the user who is the owner of the most valuable post?
gold-sql: SELECT T2.DisplayName FROM posts AS T1 INNER JOIN users AS T2 ON T1.OwnerUserId = T2.Id ORDER BY T1.FavoriteCount DESC LIMIT 1

evidence: the youngest user refers to MIN(Age);
gold-question: What is the id of the youngest user?
gold-sql: SELECT Id FROM users WHERE Age = ( SELECT MIN(Age) FROM users )

evidence: adult users refer to Age BETWEEN 19 and 65; over 5000 upvotes refer to UpVotes > 5000;
gold-question: Identify the number of adult users who have cast over 5000 upvotes.
gold-sql: SELECT COUNT(Id) FROM users WHERE Age BETWEEN 19 AND 65 AND UpVotes > 5000

evidence: super power of "Super Strength" refers to power_name = 'Super Strength'; a height of over 200cm refers to height_cm > 200
gold-question: Among the superheroes with the super power of "Super Strength", how many of them have a height of over 200cm?
gold-sql: SELECT COUNT(T1.id) FROM superhero AS T1 INNER JOIN hero_power AS T2 ON T1.id = T2.hero_id INNER JOIN superpower AS T3 ON T2.power_id = T3.id WHERE T3.power_name = 'Super Strength' AND T1.height_cm > 200

evidence: completing all the laps refers to time is not null; rate = divide(COUNT(raceID where time is not null), COUNT(raceID))
gold-question: What is the rate of drivers completing all the laps in the 2008 Australian Grand Prix?
gold-sql: SELECT CAST(SUM(IIF(T1.time IS NOT NULL, 1, 0)) AS REAL) * 100 / COUNT(T1.resultId) FROM results AS T1 INNER JOIN races AS T2 ON T1.raceId = T2.raceId WHERE T2.name = 'Australian GrAND Prix' AND T2.year = 2008

evidence: the youngest patient refers to MIN(BIRTHDAY);
gold-question: What are the symptoms observed by the youngest patient to ever did a medical examination? Identify their diagnosis.
gold-sql: SELECT T2.Symptoms, T1.Diagnosis FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Examination AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE T2.Symptoms IS NOT NULL ORDER BY T1.Birthday DESC LIMIT 1

evidence: Ig G lower than normal refers to IGG < 900; symptom of abortion refers to Symptoms = 'abortion';
gold-question: How many patients with an Ig G lower than normal has the symptom of abortion?
gold-sql: SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT T1.ID) FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID INNER JOIN Examination AS T3 ON T3.ID = T2.ID WHERE T2.IGG < 900 AND T3.Symptoms = 'abortion'

gold-question: How many students in the Student_Club are from the College of Engineering?
gold-sql: SELECT COUNT(T1.member_id) FROM member AS T1 INNER JOIN major AS T2 ON T1.link_to_major = T2.major_id WHERE T2.college = 'College of Engineering'
